        <abstract>
            <p>There is a primary law of growth and innate improvement. Natural selection is a secondary law that operates to "arrange the details". This is not Lamarckian, because will is not involved.</p> 
<p>Thanks for Chauncey Wright’s pamphlet [<hi rend="italic">Darwinism</hi> (1871)].</p> 
            <p>Amused by critics who say CD is metaphysically unsophisticated.</p>
        </abstract>
